        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auto-reply): surface fatal channel errors",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Surface classified rate-limit and overload runner failures in non-direct channel contexts instead of routing them to `NO_REPLY`.\n- Keep generic runner failure boilerplate silent in non-direct chats unless the existing silent-reply policy explicitly disallows silence.\n- Mark non-silent agent-run failure payloads as `isError` so downstream delivery sees them as error notices.\n\n## Upstream/channel coverage\n\nThis change is in the shared auto-reply runner before plugin-specific delivery. The visibility decision is made in `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForConversation()` from the shared `TemplateContext.ChatType` plus silent-reply policy, not from Discord-specific delivery code.\n\nThe regression tests now exercise representative non-direct surfaces through the same core path:\n\n- Discord group\n- Discord channel\n- Slack channel\n- Telegram group\n- WhatsApp group\n- Microsoft Teams channel\n\nFor those surfaces, tests assert that generic raw runner failures still resolve to `NO_REPLY` under default silent policy, while classified rate-limit and overload failures produce visible `isError` payloads.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n  - Result: passed, 177 tests.\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n  - Result: clean.\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`\n  - Result: passed.\n  - Provider: Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox.\n  - Testbox: `tbx_01kt62mj2zsghcn3anmfk57aym`.\n  - Actions run: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26867691876.\n  - Summary: `command=2m20.945s total=2m29.427s exit=0`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: fatal channel-visible rate-limit/overload failures are no longer suppressed to `NO_REPLY` in non-direct channel contexts, while generic runner failures remain silent by default.\n\nReal environment tested: Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox using the OpenClaw changed-check lane, plus focused local Vitest through the repo node wrapper.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`; `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`; `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`.\n\nEvidence after fix: regression tests assert Discord, Slack, Telegram, WhatsApp, and Microsoft Teams non-direct contexts all use the shared core route: classified rate-limit and overloaded failures produce non-`NO_REPLY` `isError` payloads, while generic raw runner failures still resolve to `NO_REPLY` under default silent-reply policy. The changed gate passed on Testbox `tbx_01kt62mj2zsghcn3anmfk57aym`.\n\nObserved result after fix: classified transient failure copy is visible for representative non-direct surfaces; generic raw runner failure copy still resolves to `NO_REPLY` under default silent-reply policy.\n\nWhat was not tested: a live Discord roundtrip with a real provider outage was not run; the behavior was validated at the shared auto-reply runner layer before channel-specific transport delivery.\n",
